BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 573.89 Td (demographic shares may eventually be interesting, but they would materially change model complexity and would make the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 561.89 Td (baseline comparison harder to interpret. For Assignment 7 baseline modeling, the preprocessing regime should remain) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 549.89 Td (intentionally simple.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 531.89 Td (No target transformation is applied at this stage. Assignment 5 made clear that the target-bearing sample currently) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 519.89 Td (stored in the repository is only a small reproducibility sample and should not be used to justify aggressive) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 507.89 Td (target-dependent engineering decisions. Therefore, the target remains in its original scale for baseline experiments,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 495.89 Td (and any later transformation of the response would need to be justified on the full thesis dataset.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 42.00 473.89 Td (E. Feature Selection Strategy) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 447.89 Td (The primary Assignment 6 pipeline does not use automatic wrapper or embedded feature selection. This is a deliberate) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 435.89 Td (design choice, not an omission. The feature space after engineering is already compact, and the EDA showed that the main) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 423.89 Td (risk is not under-selection but uncontrolled overlap among algebraically related variables. Automatic stepwise selection) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 411.89 Td (or repeated target-driven filtering at this stage would introduce instability, increase the chance of optimistic) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 399.89 Td (estimates, and make the F0 versus F1 comparison harder to interpret.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 381.89 Td (Instead, feature selection is handled as a predeclared filter-style design rule based on theory, data structure, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 369.89 Td (Assignment 5 evidence. The criteria are as follows: retain variables that are substantively linked to the research) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 357.89 Td (question, exclude variables with overwhelming missingness or metadata status, avoid simultaneous inclusion of multiple) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 345.89 Td (algebraically dependent age representations, and exclude identifiers that would create memorization rather than) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 333.89 Td (explanation. Under these rules, the baseline F0 feature set contains log_AllAges and gp_availability. The extended F1) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 321.89 Td (feature set contains log_AllAges, gp_availability, share_age_65_plus, share_female, deprivation_index, and the encoded) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 309.89 Td (HB and HSCP controls.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 291.89 Td (This strategy is reproducible because the feature lists are declared in configuration rather than chosen interactively) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 279.89 Td (after inspecting validation scores. It also avoids leakage because the inclusion or exclusion of variables is not) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 267.89 Td (learned from the held-out target values. In practical terms, the selection decision is locked before model training and) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 255.89 Td (is documented in the experiment configuration files.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 237.89 Td (Alternative selection methods were considered. Correlation-threshold filters based on the target were rejected because) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 225.89 Td (the available sample for target inspection is too small and because such filters are unstable in the presence of) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 213.89 Td (correlated predictors. Wrapper methods were rejected because they would substantially increase computational cost and) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 201.89 Td (would entangle model selection with preprocessing at a stage where the thesis objective is controlled baseline) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 189.89 Td (comparison. Embedded selection methods such as Lasso may be considered in later modeling assignments, but if used they) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 177.89 Td (must be treated as separate model families and evaluated with the same fold-wise leakage controls.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 159.89 Td (The impact on interpretability is positive. A restrained and predeclared feature set makes the subsequent coefficients) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 147.89 Td (and performance differences easier to explain. The impact on computational cost is also positive because the design) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 135.89 Td (matrix remains modest, particularly compared with what would happen if all age bands, many share summaries, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 123.89 Td (identifier-like variables were included simultaneously.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 42.00 101.89 Td (F. Pipeline Formalization and Reproducibility) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 75.89 Td (The engineering implementation follows the project architecture from Assignment 4. Configuration is YAML driven. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 63.89 Td (base configuration stores shared paths, seed, preprocessing defaults, and tracking rules. Experiment-specific files) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 51.89 Td (override only what differs between runs, primarily the feature set and model type. This means that preprocessing is not) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 279.64 24.00 Td (Page 4) Tj ET
