BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 795.89 Td (an informal notebook action. It is a declared pipeline stage with deterministic inputs and outputs. The current) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 783.89 Td (Assignment 4 repository already implements schema validation, analytical-dataset construction, manifest generation,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 771.89 Td (pipeline-contained imputation and encoding, and deterministic artifact tracking. Assignment 6 refines that foundation by) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 759.89 Td (freezing the thesis-ready transformation contract: log_AllAges replaces raw AllAges in the model matrix, incomplete sex) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 747.89 Td (bundles are excluded rather than approximated, and shuffled row-wise validation is replaced by grouped practice-aware) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 735.89 Td (splitting to reduce leakage.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 717.89 Td (The formal preprocessing contract can be described in the following sequence:) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 699.89 Td (1. Load the raw demographics table and supporting inputs from configured paths.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 681.89 Td (2. Validate required columns and parse Date.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 663.89 Td (3. Restrict the demographics table to Sex = All for aggregate population counts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 645.89 Td (4. Merge female totals by Date and PracticeCode.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 627.89 Td (5. Remove analytically invalid records such as AllAges less than or equal to zero and incomplete sex bundles.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 609.89 Td (6. Derive log_AllAges, share_age_0_14, share_age_65_plus, and share_female.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 591.89 Td (7. Join gp_availability, deprivation_index, and hospital_use_per_1000.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 573.89 Td (8. Save the processed analytical dataset together with a manifest that records file hashes, column names, row count, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 561.89 Td (   creation metadata.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 543.89 Td (9. For each experiment, define the feature subset from configuration.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 525.89 Td (10. Split the data with PracticeCode-aware validation so that the same practice does not contribute to both training and) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 513.89 Td (    held-out evaluation.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 495.89 Td (11. Inside each training fold, fit median and most-frequent imputers, StandardScaler for numeric variables, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 483.89 Td (    OneHotEncoder for categorical variables.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 465.89 Td (12. Fit the configured estimator on the transformed training matrix and apply the fitted pipeline unchanged to) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 453.89 Td (    validation or test data.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 435.89 Td (13. Save metrics, configuration snapshot, metadata, git commit hash, and the serialized fitted pipeline artifact.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 417.89 Td (In scikit-learn terms, the stateful part of the implementation is an integrated Pipeline built around a) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 405.89 Td (ColumnTransformer. Numeric columns pass through a sub-pipeline consisting of SimpleImputer\(strategy = median\), then) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 393.89 Td (StandardScaler. Categorical columns pass through SimpleImputer\(strategy = most_frequent\), then) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 381.89 Td (OneHotEncoder\(handle_unknown = ignore\). The final estimator is OLS for F0 and Ridge for F1 in the current baseline plan.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 369.89 Td (This object is fit only on training data and then serialized so that inference uses exactly the same transformations.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 351.89 Td (The separation between training and inference transformations is critical. Analytical-dataset construction is) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 339.89 Td (deterministic and can be rerun from raw inputs. In contrast, imputation parameters, scaling parameters, and the realized) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 327.89 Td (one-hot category map are learned artifacts. They belong to the trained pipeline, not to the raw dataset. By persisting) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 315.89 Td (the fitted pipeline as a model artifact, the project guarantees that the exact same transformation logic can be replayed) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 303.89 Td (for later evaluation or inference without manual reconstruction.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 285.89 Td (Reproducibility is further supported by the Assignment 4 tracking design. The processed dataset has a manifest with) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 273.89 Td (input hashes. Each training run stores metrics, metadata, a configuration snapshot, and the model artifact in) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 261.89 Td (deterministic locations derived from experiment name, configuration hash, and seed. The global seed is fixed in) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 249.89 Td (configuration. Paths are resolved relative to the project root. These design choices matter because they eliminate) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 237.89 Td (hidden local decisions and make it possible to connect every result to a specific dataset, configuration, and code) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 225.89 Td (state.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 42.00 203.89 Td (G. Impact on Experimental Design) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 177.89 Td (The preprocessing decisions above directly influence how later baseline experiments can be interpreted. First, keeping) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 165.89 Td (the data-construction layer constant across models ensures baseline comparability. F0 and F1 will be trained on the same) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 153.89 Td (cleaned analytical dataset, use the same target definition, follow the same group-aware split logic, and apply the same) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 141.89 Td (fold-wise imputation and encoding rules. The only substantive difference will be the additional explanatory features in) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 129.89 Td (F1 and, where relevant, the estimator choice. This is essential if the thesis is to claim that any improvement is due to) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 117.89 Td (demographic information rather than to a more favorable preprocessing path.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 99.89 Td (Second, the chosen pipeline reduces evaluation bias. Excluding QF metadata prevents artificial signal from sparse) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 87.89 Td (administrative flags. Log transforming AllAges reduces leverage without deleting meaningful observations. Restrained) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 75.89 Td (feature engineering avoids inflated multicollinearity. Pipeline-integrated preprocessing prevents leakage from global) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 63.89 Td (scaling or global imputation. Group-aware splitting reduces the risk that the model appears stronger simply because the) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 51.89 Td (same practice contributes similar rows to both training and testing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 279.64 24.00 Td (Page 5) Tj ET
