BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 795.89 Td (Third, the pipeline leaves room for controlled sensitivity analysis without undermining the primary comparison. It would) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 783.89 Td (be reasonable in later work to compare grouped validation against a time-aware split, or to compare HB plus HSCP against) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 771.89 Td (a simpler geography specification, but such comparisons must be defined as explicit secondary experiments. The baseline) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 759.89 Td (F0 versus F1 comparison for Assignment 7 should use one fixed preprocessing regime. This is important because changing) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 747.89 Td (transformations at the same time as changing the model would destroy interpretability.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 729.89 Td (Finally, the preprocessing choices are closely aligned with the research question. The thesis is not asking whether any) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 717.89 Td (flexible transformation can improve predictive scores. It is asking whether demographic structure adds explanatory value) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 705.89 Td (beyond a simpler operational baseline. The Assignment 6 pipeline therefore emphasizes interpretable demographic) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 693.89 Td (summaries, conservative cleaning, and strict leakage control. If the extended feature set outperforms the baseline under) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 681.89 Td (these conditions, the result will be methodologically credible. If it does not, that conclusion will also be credible) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 669.89 Td (because the evaluation will not have been distorted by hidden preprocessing advantages.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13.00 Tf 42.00 647.89 Td (Conclusion) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 621.89 Td (Assignment 5 established what the data look like; Assignment 6 fixes how the data will be transformed. The resulting) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 609.89 Td (preprocessing regime is explicit, empirically justified, and compatible with the reproducibility framework already) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 597.89 Td (present in the repository. It excludes overwhelmingly missing metadata, removes only structurally invalid records,) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 585.89 Td (transforms practice size instead of deleting large practices, uses compact and interpretable engineered demographic) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 573.89 Td (features, and ensures that all learned transformations are estimated only on training data.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 555.89 Td (This preprocessing contract is therefore suitable for the next stage of the seminar sequence. It preserves fairness) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 543.89 Td (between F0 and F1, limits leakage risk, documents every major decision, and provides a reproducible bridge from) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.50 Tf 42.00 531.89 Td (exploratory understanding to baseline modeling.) Tj ET
BT /F1 9.00 Tf 279.64 24.00 Td (Page 6) Tj ET
